>
	<div class="intro-section">
		<p class="lead">Not every fencing need requires a permanent installation. Construction projects, special events, pool safety during renovations, or protecting your property while waiting for permanent fencing—all these situations call for temporary solutions. This guide covers temporary fencing options available in Stockton and how to choose the right one for your needs.</p>
	</div>

	<h2>Common Uses for Temporary Fencing</h2>

	<h3>Construction Sites</h3>
	<ul>
		<li>Securing active construction zones</li>
		<li>OSHA compliance for job sites</li>
		<li>Protecting the public from hazards</li>
		<li>Preventing theft and vandalism</li>
		<li>Containing debris and materials</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>Special Events</h3>
	<ul>
		<li>Crowd control and flow management</li>
		<li>VIP area separation</li>
		<li>Vendor and staging area boundaries</li>
		<li>Parking lot organization</li>
		<li>Festival and fair perimeters</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>Residential Applications</h3>
	<ul>
		<li>Pool safety during construction or renovation</li>
		<li>Pet containment while awaiting permanent fence</li>
		<li>Property protection after storm damage</li>
		<li>Garden and landscaping protection</li>
		<li>Staging area during home remodeling</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>Commercial Uses</h3>
	<ul>
		<li>Parking lot management</li>
		<li>Inventory storage areas</li>
		<li>Seasonal outdoor displays</li>
		<li>Emergency property security</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>Types of Temporary Fencing</h2>

	<h3>Panel Chain Link Fencing</h3>
	<p>The most common temporary fencing option:</p>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Standard panels:</strong> 6' x 10' or 6' x 12' sections</li>
		<li><strong>Setup:</strong> Panels connect with clamps, held upright by weighted bases</li>
		<li><strong>Best for:</strong> Construction sites, large perimeters</li>
		<li><strong>Security level:</strong> Moderate</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>Crowd Control Barriers (Bike Rack Style)</h3>
	<p>Interlocking steel barriers:</p>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Standard size:</strong> 42" tall x 8' long</li>
		<li><strong>Setup:</strong> Sections interlock, stand freely</li>
		<li><strong>Best for:</strong> Events, crowd management, lines</li>
		<li><strong>Security level:</strong> Low (visual barrier primarily)</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>Portable Privacy Fencing</h3>
	<p>Solid panels for visual screening:</p>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Materials:</strong> Chain link with privacy slats, solid panels</li>
		<li><strong>Best for:</strong> Events requiring privacy, VIP areas</li>
		<li><strong>Advantages:</strong> Blocks view, reduces wind</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>Temporary Pool Fencing</h3>
	<p>Specifically designed for pool safety:</p>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Requirements:</strong> Must meet California pool barrier codes</li>
		<li><strong>Features:</strong> Self-closing gates, climb-resistant mesh</li>
		<li><strong>Height:</strong> Minimum 4 feet (5 feet recommended)</li>
		<li><strong>Best for:</strong> Pool safety during construction or before permanent fence installation</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>Construction Safety Fencing</h3>
	<p>High-visibility orange or green plastic mesh:</p>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Purpose:</strong> Visual warning, not security</li>
		<li><strong>Setup:</strong> Attaches to posts or stakes</li>
		<li><strong>Best for:</strong> Marking hazards, directing traffic</li>
		<li><strong>Limitations:</strong> Easily cut or climbed</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>Rental vs. Purchase</h2>

	<h3>When to Rent</h3>
	<ul>
		<li>Short-term needs (days to a few months)</li>
		<li>One-time events</li>
		<li>No storage space for panels</li>
		<li>Don't want maintenance responsibility</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>When to Purchase</h3>
	<ul>
		<li>Ongoing or repeated needs</li>
		<li>Long-term projects (6+ months—may be cheaper than rental)</li>
		<li>Need immediate availability</li>
		<li>Have storage space</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>Cost Estimates</h2>

	<table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 20px 0;">
		<thead>
			<tr style="background-color: #f4f4f4;">
				<th style="padding: 12px; border: 1px solid #ddd; text-align: left;">Type</th>
				<th style="padding: 12px; border: 1px solid #ddd; text-align: left;">Rental (per panel/month)</th>
				<th style="padding: 12px; border: 1px solid #ddd; text-align: left;">Purchase (per panel)</th>
			</tr>
		</thead>
		<tbody>
			<tr>
				<td style="padding: 12px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Chain link panels (6'x10')</td>
